node.text:
WHY YOU SHOULD BE GROWING THESE SHRUBS!⁠
⁠
In Martin Crawford's latest book, he shares an incredible range of useful shrubs for many different situations, large and small. He includes common fruit bushes like currants and gooseberries, and many other lesser-known shrubs with edible fruits, nuts, leaves, or other parts.⁠
⁠
PLUS they all contribute to carbon lockdown, so all of us, no matter what our gardens/plots, can help reduce the effects of climate change.⁠
⁠
It's available in print (link in bio, with a 10% discount) and eBook (access via your usual eBook provider).⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'TIPS TO HELP YOU UNWIND AFTER STUDYING.'.

Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Engage in a hobby There is no better way to relax and recharge than engaging in your hobby. Therefore, put aside those books and spend a few minutes or even hours to engage in an activity you enjoy. As you engage it, ensure that your entire mind is indulged in it. Therefore, spend time watching your favorite TV shows, listening to cool music or even go for a hike. Whatever activity you choose, make sure that it is something you enjoy. This break the studying monotony and the exam tension. help'.
Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text.

Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Getsseep some Get sleep You should never underestimate the benefits ofa of good night of sleep. One of the benefits is that it helps your brain to assimilate the new knowledge into a long-term memory so that you remember it during a test. If you have ever tried to concentrate after getting half a night's sleep, you will testify that you found it difficult to focus. Make sure that you deal with issues that can result in lack of sleep such as plagiarized papers. In order to avoid handling this effectively, make use of plagiarism checker.'.
Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text.

Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Use apps to help study You will come across a wide range of mobile apps that have been designed to help you get a better quality of life. This could be in areas like improving mental arithmetic (eg. Photomath), enhancing your language skills (eg. Grammarly) and becoming more organized (eg. Tasks). You can use a plagiarism checker to get rid of stress that comes with copy pasting a research paper. With a good use of these mobile study apps, it is possible to be more motivated and productive as you understand the learning progress.'.
Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text.

Photo by ForYou on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Grab a snack There are studies that show that certain foods exist that help to get rid of anxiety and stress. In case you are already feeling overwhelmed as you stare at the revision notes, avoid consuming foods and drinks that contain caffeine or high amounts of sugars as these will only increase your stress. A good idea would be to ensure that you are consuming healthy foods. These will help you to remain calm and hopefully enhance your brainpower Some of the snacks that can help to boost your mood include dark chocolate pistachio nuts and blueberries.'.
